claim.claim-text:
1. A high-pressure gas discharge lamp (1) comprising: 
a quartz glass lamp vessel (2) with a space (4) which is enclosed in a gastight manner by a wall (3), said wall (3) comprising mutually opposed seals (46, 47) and an inner surface (36); 
a pair of electrodes (5a, 5b) arranged opposite to one another in said space (4), each electrode (5a, 5b) comprising a tip (34) and an electrode rod (30), and each electrode (5a, 5b) being connected to a respective current lead-through (6, 7) which extends through a respective seal (46, 47) to the exterior; 
an outer surface (15) of the wall (3) extending between the seals (46, 47), the wall (3) having a wall load of at least 30 W/cm2 at its outer surface (15) during stable lamp operation; 
a filling inside the space (4) comprising a rare gas and halides of tin and indium, said filling comprising an alkali halide with at least one alkali ion and at least one halide ion, said alkali ion being chosen from the group formed by potassium, rubidium, and cesium, and said halide ion being chosen from the group formed by chlorine, bromine, and iodine, 
wherein the electrode rod (30) of at least one of the electrodes (5a, 5b) is provided with spacer means (8) at the area of the inner surface (36) of the wall (3), whereby a capillary opening (50) is realized which surrounds the electrode rod (30) and is present between the electrode rod (30) and the spacer means (8).
